## Task 3 – Coding and Collaboration Platforms

In Task 3, I explored online coding and collaboration platforms that are useful for students in academics and skill development. For the coding practice part, I created an account on HackerRank and solved a beginner-level programming problem. This activity helped me understand how coding practice platforms work and how they can be used to improve programming skills, logical thinking, and problem-solving ability. Platforms like HackerRank are very helpful for students to practice coding regularly and prepare for technical interviews in the future.

In the collaboration part of this task, I created a Google Form titled “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz” which included five questions related to digital literacy, internet safety, professional communication, and digital tools. I also viewed the responses in Google Sheets, which showed how data collected from forms can be automatically organized and stored in spreadsheets.

Through this task, I learned the importance of online coding platforms and cloud-based collaboration tools. These tools will be very useful for assignments, surveys, quizzes, and collaborative academic work during my college years.
